# Architecture Decisions

Several major architectural principles were established.

## Persistent Intelligence

Research results should never be transient.

Every analysis must generate reusable knowledge that can be referenced by future AI systems.

---

## Workspace-first Architecture

Every Research Job owns a complete isolated workspace.

This greatly simplifies reproducibility, debugging and artifact management.

---

## Runtime-driven Processing

Long-running processing should execute through background runtime workers instead of synchronous requests.

---

## Knowledge before Automation

Automation is valuable only if it produces structured knowledge.

The Research Center therefore focuses on building reusable intelligence rather than simply executing analysis.

